// Dashboard Design Checklist for Staff+ Engineers
// Use this when creating or reviewing a team dashboard

[ ] Top-left position: SLO attainment (big number + color)
[ ] Error budget remaining (absolute + burn rate)
[ ] Latency: p50, p95, p99 with 7d trend overlay
[ ] Error rate: 5xx percentage with breakdown by endpoint
[ ] Throughput: requests/sec with daily/weekly seasonality
[ ] Saturation: CPU, memory, connection pool, DB connections
[ ] Business metric: revenue or conversion correlated to latency
[ ] Deployment marker: show when changes were shipped
[ ] Alert history: recent triggered/resolved alerts
[ ] Action link: one-click link to runbook or incident channel

// Anti-patterns to avoid:
// - Adding charts because the data is "interesting"
// - Using pie charts (humans cannot compare angles)
// - Mixing time scales without clear labels
// - Showing raw counts without rates (10 errors = bad? depends)

// FAANG rule: If a chart has not been looked at in 30 days, remove it.
// If someone complains, add it back. This keeps dashboards lean.
